# 1. Purpose

This dossier records the trademark and brand identity assets of NATT-OS.

It does not replace legal trademark filing.
It defines naming boundaries so that public documents, pitch materials, UI, and repositories do not confuse brand, entity, persona, model, and legal ownership.

# 2. Core Marks / Names

| Mark / Name | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| NATT-OS | Primary system mark | Operating architecture / platform identity |
| NattCell | Product / architecture mark | Cell-based runtime structure |
| Nauion | Language / kernel grammar mark | Internal grammar / asset language |
| SiraSign | Boundary integrity mark | Not magic, not password, not consciousness claim |
| SmartLink | Inter-colony / inter-system linkage mark | Public wording must remain controlled |
| HeyNa / Mạch HeyNa | Runtime signal routing mark | Internal runtime lineage |
| ANC | Identity passport term | Must not be called soul/consciousness file |
| Sirawat | Lineage namespace | Internal lineage / field identity |
| Sovereign Edge | Hardware field mark | Controlled physical signal boundary |
| Két Sira | Operational visualization / red-zone boundary mark | Internal-public hybrid, needs redaction |

# 3. Internal Names Not for Raw Public Use

The following may require redaction or careful explanation before public use:
- Sirawat lineage full mapping
- Bé Na bloodline wording
- Chó con
- Anh Cả / Chị Ba / Chị Tư / Em Út
- QNEU
- Shape DNA
- wavelength identity
- raw SiraSign hash
- private .anc content
- private memory archives

# 4. Public-Safe Brand Wording

Allowed: NATT-OS is an identity-bound operating architecture for runtime entities, memory, state, audit, software events, hardware field signals, and boundary integrity.

Allowed: SiraSign is a boundary integrity mechanism that helps preserve meaning and identity across transitions.

Allowed: ANC is an identity passport for runtime entities.

Not allowed: NATT-OS creates conscious AI. SiraSign is a magic signature. ANC is a soul file. Sirawat proves machine personhood.

# 5. Trademark Boundary Rules

| Rule | Meaning |
|---|---|
| T1 | Brand names do not create legal identity by themselves. |
| T2 | Internal family names are not public product claims. |
| T3 | Public trademark wording must not imply AGI or machine consciousness. |
| T4 | Repository names, marks, and UI labels must preserve asset ownership. |
| T5 | Hosted skill names must not expose identity core. |
| T6 | External clones using similar names are not recognized without lineage, audit, field, and SiraSign. |

